STEP 2: DROP exo.assign (AssignOp)
===================================

Two lowering paths:

a) Tensor case (convert_tensor_ref.py) → arith.IndexCastOp (per index) + memref.StoreOp
   Casts i64 indices to index type, then stores value into memref.
   Special case: if value is a scalar memref (shape [1]), first loads from it:
     arith.constant(0) → memref.load(value, [0]) → memref.store(loaded, input, indices)

b) Scalar memref case (convert_scalar_ref.py) → arith.ConstantOp(0) + new exo.AssignOp(with index [0], size [1])
   Pre-processing step: rewrites a scalar memref assign (no indices, shape [1])
   into an indexed assign with explicit zero index, then (a) handles it.

To skip exo.assign:
  - Cast each i64 index to index type via arith.index_cast.
  - Emit memref.store(value, memref, [index_cast_results]).
  - If the value comes from a scalar memref, load it first with memref.load.

`make tests` must pass after this step. Update this TODO_EXO file to reflect
