STEP 3: DROP exo.window (WindowOp)
===================================

Two lowering paths:

a) Main lowering (convert_tensor_ref.py) → arith.muli + arith.index_cast + memref.subview
   Computes strides (product of input sizes), offsets (index * stride), converts everything
   to index type, then emits memref.subview with computed offsets/sizes/strides and a
   StridedLayoutAttr on the result type.

b) Memory space propagation (convert_memory_space.py) → new exo.WindowOp with memory space set
   Pre-processing: copies the input's memory space to the output type, then (a) handles it.

To skip exo.window:
  - Compute strides manually: stride[i] = product of input_sizes[i+1:].
  - Compute offsets: offset[i] = index[i] * stride[i].
  - Cast everything to index type.
  - Emit memref.subview(input, offsets, output_sizes, strides) with a StridedLayoutAttr.
  - The result memref type needs a StridedLayoutAttr matching the computed strides.

`make tests` must pass after this step. Update this TODO_EXO file to reflect
