STEP 4: CONSOLIDATE REWRITE FILES
====================================

After steps 1-3 shrink the exo dialect, merge rewrite files that handle
overlapping concerns. Current file layout in xdsl_exo/rewrites/:

  convert_tensor_ref.py    — exo read/assign/window → memref ops
  convert_scalar_ref.py    — scalar exo read/assign → 1-D memref wrappers
  convert_memory_space.py  — memory space propagation on window
  convert_memref_to_llvm.py — memref.AllocOp (DRAM) → malloc/free
  convert_blas.py          — VEC_AVX2 dealloc erasure + mm256_* intrinsics → vector/LLVM
  convert_avx2.py          — mm256_* intrinsics → LLVM (duplicates convert_blas.py)
  reconcile_index_casts.py — remove redundant arith.index_cast
  extended_memref_to_ptr.py — memref.cast/reinterpret_cast → ptr ops

Merge candidates:

  a) convert_avx2.py → merge into convert_blas.py
     Near-complete overlap: both handle mm256_* AVX2 intrinsic lowering.

  b) convert_tensor_ref.py + convert_scalar_ref.py → single file
     Both handle exo.ReadOp and exo.AssignOp, just for different shapes.
     After dropping the exo ops (steps 1-2) these may naturally collapse.

  c) convert_memory_space.py + convert_memref_to_llvm.py → single file
     Sequential stages of the same pipeline: memory space annotation →
     malloc/free lowering.

  d) convert_blas.py + convert_memref_to_llvm.py (after merge c)
     Both handle memref deallocation, dispatched by memory space
     (DRAM vs VEC_AVX2). Could become a single alloc-lowering file.

Do this after dropping exo ops — the merges will be cleaner once there are
fewer ops to route between files.

